![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/bannernewsletter.png)

Welcome to July's Turing-Roche newsletter! Here you can find what's new in the Turing-Roche strategic partnership and opportunities, events and news from both The Alan Turing Institute and Roche.

Our [five year partnership](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FbIdVI6LgLzYDAY8aFM_2sw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C5c6d5876dd784bdec80308da60c3d3fe%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637928691447726648%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=Szaa22aoI1YuX6cpJBIisQZNsOOwfXrFFFO1ykMSVz8%3D&reserved=0) was set up officially in June 2021 following a successful [Data Study Group](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2F3k0pS6yGmtoBPTyipU2UXQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C5c6d5876dd784bdec80308da60c3d3fe%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637928691447726648%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=H%2BAt741MIjU7NkUkuq0H4sjgHbwfGgezQjRj3DG%2FB7k%3D&reserved=0) and a 12 week research project on lung cancer treatment. Our 'North Star' is **to enable the generation of insights to better understand patient and disease heterogeneity and its relevance to clinical outcomes at an unprecedented level of precision in order to improve clinical care. **

We will be covering multiple activities over the five years to work towards our North Star, as well as building strong connections and collaborations between the Alan Turing Institute, Roche and the wider community.

If you have anything you'd like featured in a future newsletter then please get in touch with Vicky Hellon, Community Manager for the partnership at <vhellon@turing.ac.uk>

If you would like to share this newsletter with relevant colleagues please direct them to sign-up [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FoGouPNt_36Kp0ntMBxF-Og&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C5c6d5876dd784bdec80308da60c3d3fe%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637928691447882854%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=3NAWXHYbzqlHGLLsnDUjEWDRAsxWdgGDpqBfwrlW7T8%3D&reserved=0).

### Knowledge Share Series Event: Synthetic Data

**25 July 2022**

Join us for our newly launched [partnership knowledge share series](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2Fi8Q8_lSuVadoEM4CdtNyVQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C5c6d5876dd784bdec80308da60c3d3fe%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637928691447882854%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=TyrxP%2FgokrxFdVdvS3ZWM55GOOfb5vtCn6x6ATOjYso%3D&reserved=0)! Our aim is to bring together members of the Turing and Roche networks and beyond to share different academic and industry perspectives on areas related to patient/treatment heterogeneity and data science more generally.

July's event is on the 25th on the topic of Synthetic Data. We'll be hearing perspectives on this growing area from Florimond Houssiau, Research Associate at the Alan Turing Institute and Marta Battle and Finn Janson who are both Data Scientists at Roche. You can register for the event [here](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%%2FhV7sjmyPVn-ThO5qKRYJdQ&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C5c6d5876dd784bdec80308da60c3d3fe%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637928691447882854%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=l6t0lyxw171GwIdV7fHyzhNfaw2yM2wNHtIZ3BY1aSI%3D&reserved=0).

### Turing Institute recruiting 3 Co-Directors for new Research and Innovation Cluster in Digital Twins 

**Deadline 20 July 2022**

The Turing Institute is establishing a new Research and Innovation Cluster in Digital Twins (TRIC-DT) to support research and innovation at the interface of AI and DT technologies, ensuring UK leadership in these technologies. This cluster will work closely with partner organisations and coordinate activity with other national DT initiatives to extend the Institute's substantial DT research and innovation activity, and will explicitly focus on solving significant societal challenges and generating tangible societal benefits in three interrelated areas of Environment and Sustainability, Infrastructure and Health. We are now recruiting the leadership team for this cluster. ### Turing AI for Multiple Long Term Conditions Research Support Facility Seminar:****New findings from age-dependent topic modelling of Multiple Long-term Conditions in UK Biobank**

**12 July 2022**

## Publication of the Month

![](https://file-eu.clickdimensions.com/turingacuk-ap7zg/files/patrick-tomasso-oaqk7qqnh_c-unsplash2.jpg)

**Systematic pan-cancer analysis of mutation--treatment interactions using large real-world clinicogenomics data**

July's publication of the month is [this paper](https://eur01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=http%3A%2F%2Felink.turing.ac.uk%2Fc%2F7%_X2NsZGVlPU9uakttU0lENlUtcDhVUF9ncXkzWkJORk5UdFZabnczekdLQk16OUlJdnBnWFFqLVNmYUFNWGw5dFZobDFGUk0mcmVjaXBpZW50aWQ9Y29udGFjdC00ODgwYThjMzkyM2NlYzExOGM2MjAwMjI0ODQzNGZlYi1iMWI4OTBhMzk5YWI0NDM1YWU1ZDRkZGM5ZWEzYWU5YyZlc2lkPTcwMDYwODYyLTBlZmQtZWMxMS04MmU2LTAwMGQzYWQ1ODdjZSJ9%2FxgPPo1BqPUPObtDDWpuwBw&data=05%7C01%7Cvhellon%40turing.ac.uk%7C5c6d5876dd784bdec80308da60c3d3fe%7C4395f4a7e4554f958a9f1fbaef6384f9%7C0%7C0%7C637928691447882854%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=koG%2F2OWkga4jnIjRYJv88kh9iDnK7WfBHwGYlsa3kSU%3D&reserved=0) detailing the results of a large scale computational analysis of over 40,000 cancer patients- identifying 458 mutations that predict survival on targeted therapies. Published in Nature Medicine, this paper is authored by some of our Roche partnership team members (Chris Harbron and Ryan Copping) as well as other Roche/Genetech employees and their Stanford University colleagues. The work demonstrates how computational analysis of real-world data can generate insights that can enable precision oncology.
